  "description": [
    "ItTHE CATHOLIC TIMES Friday April 291955 4 3 Sr ri A Prayer for Peace Premier Ngo Dinh Diem of South Vietnam a devout Catholic pray for peace and unity of hi troubled country at a religious service held in the chapel of th Independence Palace in Saigot Hollywood Ads in Orient Harming US Prestige By Father Patrick 0Connor Society of St Columban N C W C NEWS SERVICE MANILA Hollywood sends movie advertisements to the Far East that are morally offensive and harmful to United States prestige It has been doing it for years I have seen specimens all the wav from Tokyo to Manila from Hong Kong to Peking It supplies advertisements in poster form and in ready made mats for newspaper use In these advertisements it is common to find a lurid jargon of sex violence and crime Cheesecake art is common Some times suggestive pictures are add ed to suggestive words Examples from ads seen in news papers and on posters during re eent visits to Manila For a film with the title Human Desire the ad offers this line as sales talk She Was Born to Be Bad to be Kissed to Make Trouble To pack"
